Build ubuntu-uefi sdcard image for raspberrypi5:

cd ~/Downloads
wget https://cdimage.ubuntu.com/noble/daily-live/current/noble-desktop-arm64.iso
wget https://github.com/worproject/rpi5-uefi/releases/download/v0.3/RPi5_UEFI_Release_v0.3.zip

cd ~/build-raspberrypi5/ubuntu-uefi

Plugin sdcard to PC.
sudo ./mkuefiboot.sh
sudo mkfs.vfat /dev/sda1
sudo fdisk -l /dev/sda
sudo mount -t vfat /dev/sda1 /mnt
cd /mnt
sudo 7z x ~/Downloads/RPi5_UEFI_Release_v0.3.zip
cd ~/build-raspberrypi5/ubuntu-uefi
sync
sudo umount /mnt
Eject sdcard from PC.

Plugin USB2 flash drive to PC.
sudo ./mksdcardimg.sh
sudo mkfs.vfat /dev/sda1
sudo fdisk -l /dev/sda
sudo mount -t vfat /dev/sda1 /mnt
cd /mnt
sudo 7z x ~/Downloads/oracular-desktop-arm64.iso
sudo 7z x ~/Downloads/RPi5_UEFI_Release_v0.3.zip
cd ~/build-raspberrypi5/ubuntu-uefi
sync
sudo umount /mnt
Eject USB2 flash drive from PC.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
Install ubuntu from ubuntu iso in USB2 flash drive to sdcard.
------------------------------------------------------------------------

Plugin sdcard and USB2 flash drive to rpi5. Plugin usb wifi dongle to rpi5. Power on rpi5.
Select install
Select alongside another OS and install Ubuntu.
Contine till finished. Restart.

Remove USB2 flash drive from rpi5.
Login:
Username: linaro
Password: linaro
Disable power saving and screen saver.
sudo apt install net-tools openssh-server pulseaudio-utils pavucontrol
uname -a
lsb_release -a
sudo ifconfig
sudo dpkg-reconfigure tzdata
sudo dpkg-reconfigure locales
date
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sudo apt dist-upgrade
sync
sudo shutdown -h now
Power off, power on
glxinfo | grep OpenGL
date
Check if Ubuntu is running UEFI mode:
ls /sys/firmware/efi
Check display mode: ( wayland or x11 )
echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE
Check audio driver: ( pulseaudio or pipewire )
pactl info

sudo apt install speedtest-cli python3-pip python3-setuptools ffmpeg mpv glmark2-es2-wayland pandoc

speedtest-cli --secure

glmark2-es2-wayland

aplay -l
pavucontrol  ( select card 0 as default )

firefox -> youtube.com -> search YmDNhi07_Ho

git clone https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp.git
cd yt-dlp
make
cd ../
~/yt-dlp/yt-dlp -f 'bestvideo[ext=mp4]+bestaudio[ext=m4a]' 3qrKjywjo7Q -o swan.mp4
mpv swan.mp4

sudo rfkill list
hciconfig hci0
hcitool dev
hciconfig -a

rpi5 sound, wifi, ethernet and bluetooth are not supported in mainline kernel 6.8.0-50-generic or 6.11.0-9-generic.

----------------------------------------------
Compile mainline kernel
----------------------------------------------

sudo apt install make build-essential libncurses-dev bison flex libssl-dev libelf-dev
wget https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/snapshot/linux-6.13-rc1.tar.gz
tar -xzf linux-6.13-rc1.tar.gz
mv linux-6.13-rc1 linux
cd linux
sudo make mrproper
make ARCH=arm64 defconfig
make ARCH=arm64 all -j8
sudo make ARCH=arm64 modules_install
sudo make ARCH=arm64 dtbs_install
sudo make ARCH=arm64 install
sudo vi /boot/grub/grub.cfg ( change first menu to:
linux   /boot/vmlinuz-6.13.0-rc1
initrd  /boot/initrd.img-6.13.0-rc1
devicetree /boot/dtbs/6.13.0-rc1/broadcom/bcm2712-rpi-5-b.dtb
)
sync
sudo reboot

